The small plane of Steve Fossett, the billionaire who disappeared on a flight over the Nevada desert on September 3, 2007, was found.
The individual pieces were found on a 3,000-meter high plateau in the Sierra Nevada Mammoth Lakes area between the states of California and Nevada.
However, no human remains were found inside the plane.
Madera County Sheriff John Anderson fully cleared the last of the doubts during a press conference: "The plane has been located, and a force has been deployed, and we now have the certainty that it was the plane that Steve Fossett was flying on the day he disappeared".
Mr. Anderson also confirmed that no human remains were found in or near the plane.
The 63-year-old billionaire was declared dead in February.
